(
Figs 1
, 

5– 
6

) in dorsal view (

Fig. 
1

) indistinctly bell-shaped, broadest in front of middle; anterior corners indistinct, posterior corners obtuse-angled and blunt. Pronotum lacking any carinae, pits, grooves or impressions. Prosternum (

Fig. 
6

) nearly half as long as pronotum, with basisternal part (

Fig. 
6

; 
bst
) very long, several times longer than coxal part and distinctly demarcated from procoxal cavities (

